Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Alexis> how is it going everyone

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> If you install the new version and had previously used a password with a saved seed, those will still work. If you previously had used your seed to login lite mode you can still do that but under the restore setting. This will let you use your seed and then save that seed and secure it with a password, so that you can login with that password alone. (re @Marcauj: Does it mean we have to export the private key first on the older version then use the private key to restore the wallet on the new agama ?)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> This way you don't have to keep typing or copying and pasting your entire seed to login to lite mode.
